cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for learning distributed representations of words and phrases. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses improvements in training speed and quality, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of negative sampling and subsampling of frequent words indicates that it could also be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses finding phrases in text, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the use of vector representations for words and phrases suggests that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
